                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-blue-600 mb-2">Activity 1: The Human Tree</h2>
                <p class="text-center text-slate-500 mb-8">(20 minutes)</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <p class="text-lg mb-6">Let's build a tree using people! We'll use this to learn the core terminology.</p>
                    <!-- Visual representation of the human tree -->
                    <div class="relative w-full max-w-xl mx-auto h-96">
                        <!-- SVG lines (edges) -->
                        <svg class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full" style="z-index: 1;">
                           <line x1="50%" y1="48" x2="calc(50% - 100px)" y2="152" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2"/>
                           <line x1="50%" y1="48" x2="calc(50% + 100px)" y2="152" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2"/>
                           <line x1="calc(50% - 100px)" y1="192" x2="calc(50% - 150px)" y2="272" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2"/>
                           <line x1="calc(50% - 100px)" y1="192" x2="calc(50% - 50px)" y2="272" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2"/>
                        </svg>
                        <!-- Nodes -->
                        <div class="absolute w-24 h-24 tree-node bg-red-500" style="left: 50%; top: 0; transform: translateX(-50%); z-index: 2;">Root</div>
                        <div class="absolute w-20 h-20 tree-node bg-blue-500" style="left: calc(50% - 100px); top: 152px; transform: translateX(-50%); z-index: 2;">Left-Child</div>
                        <div class="absolute w-20 h-20 tree-node bg-blue-500" style="left: calc(50% + 100px); top: 152px; transform: translateX(-50%); z-index: 2;">Right-Child</div>
                        <div class="absolute w-16 h-16 tree-node bg-green-500 text-sm" style="left: calc(50% - 150px); top: 272px; transform: translateX(-50%); z-index: 2;">Leaf</div>
                        <div class="absolute w-16 h-16 tree-node bg-green-500 text-sm" style="left: calc(50% - 50px); top: 272px; transform: translateX(-50%); z-index: 2;">Leaf</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                 <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-slate-700">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-blue-600">Key Terms</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
                            <li><span class="font-semibold">Root:</span> The single top-most node.</li>
                            <li><span class="font-semibold">Parent:</span> A node with children.</li>
                            <li><span class="font-semibold">Left/Right-Child:</span> Nodes below a parent.</li>
                            <li><span class="font-semibold">Leaf:</span> A node with NO children.</li>
                            <li><span class="font-semibold">Subtree:</span> A parent and all its descendants.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-blue-800">Recursive Thinking</h3>
                        <p class="mt-2">How can we describe a tree? "A tree is a <span class="font-semibold">root</span> node, connected to a left <span class="font-semibold">subtree</span> and a right <span class="font-semibold">subtree</span>."</p>
                        <p class="mt-2 italic">A subtree is just a smaller tree. The structure is defined in terms of itself!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
             <a href="#activity2" class="mt-8 text-blue-500">↓ Next Activity</a>
